If you are upgrading from a release which is <= v1.0.2 the following changes are recommended to the sync database for better compatibility with future releases.

*************** WARNING ***************
DO NOT perform any/all of the steps mentioned below before creating a reliable backup of the database. Check Backup section of Data management page in the Wiki for more details.

*************** IMPORTANT ***************
Make the application offline before performing the below mentioned steps to avoid unpredictable changes to the data/database.


#### MariaDB / Mysql

# Execute below SQL statements to alter required table(s).
ALTER TABLE cards_addressbook MODIFY COLUMN user_specific CHAR(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1', MODIFY COLUMN writable CHAR(1) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1';
ALTER TABLE propertystorage MODIFY COLUMN path TEXT NOT NULL, MODIFY COLUMN name TEXT NOT NULL, MODIFY COLUMN valuetype INTEGER;

# Execute SQL statements from below mentioned files(s) in this release.
sql/mysql/30_trigger_ddl.sql


#### PostgreSQL

# Execute below SQL statements to alter required table(s).
ALTER TABLE cards_addressbook ALTER COLUMN user_specific TYPE CHAR(1) USING (user_specific::INTEGER), ALTER COLUMN user_specific SET DEFAULT '1', ALTER COLUMN writable TYPE CHAR(1) USING (writable::INTEGER), ALTER COLUMN writable SET DEFAULT '1';
ALTER TABLE propertystorage ALTER COLUMN path TYPE TEXT, ALTER COLUMN name TYPE TEXT, ALTER COLUMN valuetype TYPE INTEGER;

# Execute SQL statements from below mentioned files(s) in this release.
sql/pgsql/30_trigger_ddl.sql


#### SQLite

# Create target database as per "-- Sync database creation" section in the INSTALL file.
